## 🫐 Acai-TypeScript — What's Inside

**1,678 files rebranded — 0 remaining Amplitude references.**

### What was changed
- All `@amplitude/*` package names → `@acai/*` (browser, node, react-native, all plugins)
- All server URLs → `https://events.acai.yourdomain.com/2/httpapi`
- All internal constants (`AMPLITUDE_PREFIX`, `AMPLITUDE_SERVER_URL`, `__AMPLITUDE_MESSENGER__`, etc.) → `ACAI_*`
- Storage prefix changed from `AMP_` → `ACAI_`
- All READMEs, examples, test files, config files rebranded

### New files added
- **`ingest-server/`** — A complete TypeScript ingest server with:
  - `/2/httpapi` and `/batch` endpoints (SDK-compatible)
  - API key validation
  - Pluggable storage (swap in Postgres, ClickHouse, Kafka)
  - Optional admin debug route
  - Docker-ready
- **`setup.sh`** — One-command setup for new contributors

---

### Getting started (after downloading)

```bash
unzip Acai-TypeScript.zip && cd Acai-TypeScript

# 1. Build the SDK
nvm use && yarn install && yarn build

# 2. Start your ingest server
cd ingest-server
cp .env.example .env         # Set ACAI_API_KEY=your_key
npm install && npm run dev

# 3. In your app
npm install @acai/analytics-browser

acai.init('your_key', { serverUrl: 'http://localhost:3000/2/httpapi' });
acai.track('Hello World');
```

> Replace `events.acai.yourdomain.com` with your real domain in `packages/analytics-core/src/types/constants.ts` before publishing to npm.